Since C++ doesn't have built-in reflection, you can't directly ask an object for its type at runtime. However, you can use a mix of virtual functions and `dynamic_cast` to downcast `Args*` to the appropriate derived type in a type-safe manner.

First, ensure that your `Args` class has a virtual function that can identify the type. I see that you have already set up flags like `type_int_`, `type_string_`, and `type_bool_` in derived classes. Instead, I'd recommend using a virtual function that returns an enum representing the type, as it is cleaner and safer.

