The advantage of this method is that you are giving each derived class the responsibility to report its own type, which upholds the design principle of encapsulation. Additionally, this approach is less error-prone than maintaining separate type flags in each class.

If you prefer to use flags to denote the type of each `Args` derivative, you need to ensure that you have a flag in each derived class and then implement a getter in the base class `Args` to enable the identification of the derived class type. Here is an implementation using your flags for type identification:

